data.chText: 空的
data.enText: with no people or things inside

data.chText: 空盒 / 杯
data.enText: an empty box/glass

data.chText: 空手
data.enText: empty hands (= not holding anything)

data.chText: 空盘子
data.enText: an empty plate (= with no food on it)

data.chText: 剧场只坐了一半观众。
data.enText: The theatre was half empty .

data.chText: 空着的房子 / 房间 / 公共汽车
data.enText: an empty house/room/bus

data.chText: 这张椅子没人坐吗？
data.enText: Is this an empty chair (= not one that another person will be using) ?

data.chText: 这房子已经有一段时间没住人了。
data.enText: The house had been standing empty (= without people living in it) for some time.

data.chText: 空腹喝酒不好。
data.enText: It's not good to drink alcohol on an empty stomach (= without having eaten something) .

data.chText: 房间里什么家具都没有。
data.enText: The room was empty of furniture.

data.chText: 空洞的；说话不算数的；无诚意的

before.enText: of sth that sb says or does

data.enText: with no meaning; not meaning what is said

data.chText: 空话
data.enText: empty words

data.chText: 兑现不了的承诺
data.enText: an empty promise

data.chText: 旨在取悦观众的装腔作势
data.enText: an empty gesture aimed at pleasing the crowds

data.chText: 空虚的；无意义的；无目的的

before.enText: of a person, or a person's life

data.enText: unhappy because life does not seem to have a purpose, usually after sth sad has happened

data.chText: 他死后三个月她仍然感到心里很空虚。
data.enText: Three months after his death, she still felt empty.

data.chText: 没有你，我的生活似乎就没有了意义。
data.enText: My life seems empty without you.

data.chText: 没有；缺乏；无
data.enText: without a quality that you would expect to be there

data.chText: 无意义的话
data.enText: words that were empty of meaning

data.chText: 她站着茫然地凝视远方。
data.enText: She stood staring emptily into space.
empties
emptying
emptied
emptied

data.chText: 倒空；腾空；掏空
data.enText: to remove everything that is in a container, etc.

data.chText: 我把口袋里的东西都掏了出来，仍然找不到我的钥匙。
data.enText: I emptied out my pockets but could not find my keys.

data.chText: 她把水从花瓶里倒了出来。
data.enText: She emptied the water out of the vase.

data.chText: 他喝了一杯，又要求再斟满一杯。
data.enText: He emptied his glass and asked for a refill.

data.chText: 他倒掉烟灰缸里的灰，洗完杯子就上床睡觉了。
data.enText: He emptied the ashtrays, washed the glasses and went to bed.

data.chText: 屋里所有的家具都搬走了。
data.enText: The room had been emptied of all furniture.

data.chText: 她打消了想家的所有念头。
data.enText: She emptied her mind of all thoughts of home.

data.chText: 变空
data.enText: to become empty

data.chText: 大容器里的液体五分钟就流干了。
data.enText: The tank empties out in five minutes.

data.chText: 雨下起来时街上很快便空无一人。
data.enText: The streets soon emptied when the rain started.

data.chText: 把…移出，把…腾出（置于别处）
data.enText: to take out the contents of sth and put them somewhere else

data.chText: 她把包里的东西全倒在了桌子上。
data.enText: She emptied the contents of her bag onto the table.

data.chText: 许多工厂都将污水排进了这条河里。
data.enText: Many factories emptied their waste into the river.

data.chText: （把…）撤出，撤离；撤空
data.enText: to make sure that everyone leaves a room, building, etc.

data.chText: 由于炸弹的威胁，警方奉命将人撤离这栋大楼。
data.enText: Police had instructions to empty the building because of a bomb threat.

data.chText: 流入；涌进
data.enText: to flow or move out from one place to another

data.chText: 莱茵河注入北海。
data.enText: The Rhine empties into the North Sea.

data.chText: 音乐会结束后，乐迷涌到大街上。
data.enText: Fans emptied out onto the streets after the concert.

means: 把…移出，把…腾出(置于别处)

synonyms.bx: 指纸张无字迹的、未印刷过的，或磁带未录制内容的。

ex.chText: 她在那个空荡荡的小房间住了6年。
ex.enText: She lived in that tiny bare room for six years.

ex.chText: 她穿着一件低领连衣裙，手臂裸露。
ex.enText: She wore a low-necked dress, and her arms were bare.

ex.chText: 卧室里地板裸露，没有铺地毯。
ex.enText: There's no carpet in the bedroom, just bare floorboards.

synonyms.bx: 指建筑物内部缺乏设施或装饰的，也指人身体部位裸露的，形容土地、树木等时表示其没有植被覆盖或枝叶凋落的。

ex.chText: 这房子好多年没人住了。
ex.enText: The house stood empty for many years.

synonyms.bx: 指容器里面什么也没有或者某个地方没有人的。

ex.chText: 使用空心砖是因为它们更轻。
ex.enText: Hollow blocks are used because they are lighter.

synonyms.bx: 指实物的内部是空心的。

ex.chText: 他辞职后，这个职位暂时空缺。
ex.enText: The position became vacant after his resignation.

synonyms.bx: 指房屋、土地等未被占用的，或指工作或职位空缺的，侧重表示临时性的情况。

tr: a container that has been emptied
example: return all empties to the store

tr: excrete or discharge from the body
become empty or void of its content
make void or empty of contents

example: You must vacate your office by tonight
after the violent argument he felt empty
after skipped lunch the men were empty by suppertime

value.def: An empty place, vehicle, or container is one that has no people or things in it.

example.ex: The room was bare and empty.
The roads were nearly empty of traffic.

value.def: An empty gesture, threat, or relationship has no real value or meaning.

example.ex: His father threatened to throw him out, but he knew it was an empty threat.
example.tran: 他父亲威胁要把他赶出去，但他知道那只不过是吓吓他罢了。

example.ex: ...to ensure the event is not perceived as an empty gesture.
example.tran: 确保这一活动不被看作只是一种空洞的姿态

value.tran: (威胁、关系等)空洞的，无意义的，无效的

value.def: If you describe a person's life or a period of time as empty, you mean that nothing interesting or valuable happens in it.

example.ex: My life was very hectic but empty before I met him.
example.tran: 在遇到他之前，我的生活非常繁忙却很空虚。

value.tran: (生活或某段时间)空虚的，枯燥无味的

value.def: If you feel empty, you feel unhappy and have no energy, usually because you are very tired or have just experienced something upsetting.

example.ex: I felt empty and hollow; defeated...
example.tran: 我感觉空虚无聊，充满挫败感。

example.ex: I feel so empty, my life just doesn't seem worth living any more.
example.tran: 我觉得非常空虚，生活似乎根本不值得继续下去。

value.def: If you empty a container, or empty something out of it, you remove its contents, especially by tipping it up.

example.ex: Empty the noodles and liquid into a serving bowl...
example.tran: 把汤面倒进上菜用的碗中。

example.ex: He emptied the contents out into the palm of his hand.
example.tran: 他把东西都倒在手心里。

value.def: If someone empties a room or place, or if it empties, everyone that is in it goes away.

example.ex: The stadium emptied at the end of the first day of athletics.
example.tran: 首日比赛结束后，体育场空无一人。

example.ex: ...a woman who could empty a pub full of drunks just by lifting one fist.
example.tran: 只要举起一只拳头就能把一酒吧的醉鬼全部赶跑的女人

value.def: A river or canal that empties into a lake, river, or sea flows into it.

example.ex: The Washougal empties into the Columbia River near Portland.
example.tran: 沃舒格尔河在波特兰附近注入哥伦比亚河。

value.def: Empties are bottles or containers which no longer have anything in them.
